-- Procter & Gamble to Build 1 Billion Egyptian-Pound Diaper Plant Near Cairo
-- Ola Galal
-- 2010-06-29T08:25:37Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-29/procter-gamble-to-build-1-billion-egyptian-pound-diaper-plant-near-cairo.html

          
          
             Procter & Gamble Co. said it plans
to build a 1 billion Egyptian pound ($175 million) diaper
factory in Egypt.  
 The plant, based in an industrial zone in the 6th of
October near Cairo, is scheduled to start production by the end
of 2011, the Cincinnati, Ohio-based company said in a statement
distributed to reporters in Cairo today.  
 Forty percent of the plantâ€™s output will be sold locally,
the company said.  
